Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Twelve (12) months jail.  Nine (9) months, under the Huber Law, to commence on 10-29-15 by 5:00 p.m.   Three (3) months, stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion;
2) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety;
5) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
6) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
7) No association with any known drug users or dealers;
8) Pay costs of action;
9) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.   
Voter Ineligibility Notice and Acknowledgment.  
